                        <img class="package-img" src="../img/angularjs-logo.svg" alt="">
                        <h3>Angular 2+ Version</h3>
                        <p class="text-white">We spent around <span class="fw-semi-bold">500</span> man-hours developing
                            and designing
                            Angular version, to match high engineering requirements.</p>
                        <p class="text-white-50"><a href="https://angular.io" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">Angular</a> is the most mature
                            and wide spread
                            front-end framework created by Google and used by many established enterprises. It is a very
                            good choice when
                            your expect your application to have a well-engineered structure and development workflow.
                            If you are familiar
                            with Java or .NET ecosystems Angular is definitely your choice.
                        </p>
                        <p class="text-white-50">Our app is built on top of latest <strong>Angular 5.0</strong> version and
                            uses <a href="https://webpack.js.org/">Webpack</a> Module Bundler and NPM as a package
                            manager, so everything
                            works out of the box! <br><br></p>
